> It appears that when podman is running GPG, its `$UID` is incorrectly set to `0`

That does sound like a plausible proximate cause; https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/23659 contains more discussion about running inside user namespaces. I can, maybe, imagine a stand-alone `podman secret` to be modified to run without switching a user namespace, but I don’t know how that would work for `podman run --secret…`

@ashley-cui you know much more about the secrets features, is there a plausible path forward?
